## ðŸŸ© Pattern 1: Solid Square

```
****
****
****
****
```

### âœ… Code:

```java
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 4; // number of rows and columns

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                System.out.print("*");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
```

---

## ðŸŸ© Pattern 2: Hollow Square

```
****
*  *
*  *
****
```

### âœ… Code:

```java
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 4;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                if (i == 0 || i == n - 1 || j == 0 || j == n - 1)
                    System.out.print("*");
                else
                    System.out.print(" ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
```

---

## ðŸŸ© Pattern 3: Right-Aligned Solid Square

```
    ****
   ****
  ****
 ****
```

### âœ… Code:

```java
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 4;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int s = n - i - 1; s > 0; s--) {
                System.out.print(" ");
            }
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                System.out.print("*");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
```

---

## ðŸŸ© Pattern 4: Repeating `*-*-*`

```
*-*-*
*-*-*
*-*-*
```

### âœ… Code:

```java
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int rows = 3;
        int cols = 5; // pattern repeats 5 columns (*-*-*)

        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
                if (j % 2 == 0)
                    System.out.print("*");
                else
                    System.out.print("-");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
```

